Key Differences: number of arguments

IFNULL (faster)
+----------------------------------------------------------------------+
Number of Arguments:	Exactly 2

Example:
SELECT IFNULL(column, 'default_value') FROM table_name;
------------------------------------------------------------------------


COALESCE (slower)
+----------------------------------------------------------------------+
Number of Arguments: 2 or more

Example:
SELECT COALESCE(column1, column2, 'default_value') FROM table_name;
------------------------------------------------------------------------
